details.floor: Hewn Stone (DC 10 to charge or run)
details.history: The dungeon was created by a lawful good ranger as a maze. It became cursed by the gods, and has lain empty for many centuries until recently.
details.illumination: Average (shadowy in corridors, lamps or torches in most rooms)

monster: 3 x Gelatinous Cube (cr 2, mm 129); high, 1350 xp

Treasure: 400 ep, a lacquered wooden bowl engraved with elven script (250 gp), Spell Scroll (Healing Word (phb 284)) (common, dmg 305), Periapt of Health (uncommon, dmg 284), Staff of the Python (uncommon, dmg 311)
detail.room_features: A stone dais and throne sits in the west side of the room, and blood drips from the ceiling in the east side of the room

monster: 3 x Giant Constrictor Snake (cr 2, mm 355); high, 1350 xp
detail.room_features: Burning torches in iron sconces line the north wall, and a rusted amulet lies in the center of the room

Spirals of red stones cover the floor, and several pieces of blood-soaked clothing are scattered throughout the room
